A banking union in which euro-area
countries jointly provide capital to financial institutions
would help stem the debt crisis, Handelsblatt quoted Swiss
National Bank President Thomas Jordan as saying in an interview.  A banking union would weaken the link between banks and
national governments and is the quickest way to deepen
integration in the European Union, the German newspaper cited
Jordan as saying in comments published today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
